      "content": "i get that the official records say it's just \"practical,\" but that's always how these things are covered up, right? the patterns are too precise to be coincidences. even and if the primary reason was \"military surveys,\" that actually makes it more suspicious because those surveys were often used to lay out ritualistic boundaries. \n\nif you look at the way the lines intersect near the old waterfront, they create these exact nodes. it's not just random. help me make sense of this—if we assume the architecture *is* doing something more than just managing traffic, what kind of purpose would a network like this serve on a global scale? like, if you see these same angled alignments in london or dc, what's the connecting thread?",
